  "prompt": "What is the weather in Orlando like on June, and how does it differ from the weather in August?",
  "response": "In **June**, the weather in Orlando, Florida, is typically hot and humid, marking the start of the summer season. Average high temperatures are around **90\u00b0F (32\u00b0C)**, while lows are around **73\u00b0F (23\u00b0C)**. Rainfall increases as the wet season begins, with frequent afternoon thunderstorms. June averages about **7.5 inches (190 mm)** of rain, spread over approximately 16 rainy days.\n\nIn **August**, the weather remains hot and humid, but it is often the peak of summer heat. Average high temperatures rise slightly to around **92\u00b0F (33\u00b0C)**, and lows are around **75\u00b0F (24\u00b0C)**. August is also the wettest month of the year in Orlando, with an average of **7.8 inches (198 mm)** of rain and an increased likelihood of thunderstorms, particularly in the late afternoon.\n\n### Key Differences:\n- **Temperature**: August is slightly hotter than June, with higher average highs and lows.\n- **Rainfall**: August tends to be wetter than June, with more intense and frequent thunderstorms due to the peak of the wet season.\n- **Humidity**: Both months are humid, but August can feel more oppressive due to the combination of higher temperatures and increased moisture in the air.\n\nOverall, both months are hot and rainy, but August tends to be more extreme in terms of heat and precipitation.",
